params.ownerAddr: The address of the owner of the Oracle to check for.

params.coinPair: coin pair to unsubscribe, for example BTCUSD

params.mocHolder: the moc holder whose mocs will be locked.
params.untilTimestamp: timestamp until which the mocs will be locked.

params.oracleAddr: address of the oracle (from which we publish prices)
params.url: url used by the oracle server

params.coinPair: coin pair to subscribe, for example BTCUSD
coin pair to unsubscribe, for example BTCUSD

canRemoveOracle(address).notice: Returns true if an oracle satisfies conditions to be removed from system.

changeIGovernor(address).notice: Change the contract's governor. Should be called through the old governance system

delegateCallToChanger(bytes).notice: This method is used by a change contract to access the storage freely even without a setter.

deposit(uint256,address).notice: Accept a deposit from an account. Delegates to the Supporters smart contract.

depositFrom(uint256,address,address).notice: Accept a deposit from an account. Delegates to the Supporters smart contract.

getBalance(address).notice: Reports the balance of MOCs for a specific user. Delegates to the Supporters smart contract.

getCoinPairAtIndex(uint256).notice: Returns the coin pair at index.

getCoinPairCount().notice: Returns the count of registered coin pairs. Keep in mind that Deleted coin-pairs will contain zeroed addresses.

getContractAddress(bytes32).notice: Return the contract address for a specified registered coin pair.

getLockedBalance(address).notice: Reports the balance of locked MOCs for a specific user. Delegates to the Supporters smart contract.

getRegisteredOracleAtIndex(uint256).notice: Returns the oracle name and address at index. Delegates to the Oracle Manager smart contract.

getRegisteredOraclesLen().notice: Returns the amount of owners registered. Delegates to the Oracle Manager smart contract.

governor().notice: The address of the contract which governs this one

isOracleRegistered(address).notice: Return true if the oracle is registered.

isSubscribed(address,bytes32).notice: Returns true if an oracle is subscribed to a coin pair

lockMocs(address,uint256).notice: Used by the voting machine to lock an amount of MOCs. Delegates to the Supporters smart contract.

registerOracle(address,string).notice: Set an oracle's name (url) and address. Delegates to the Oracle Manager smart contract.

removeOracle().notice: Remove an oracle. Delegates to the Oracle Manager smart contract.

subscribeToCoinPair(bytes32).notice: Subscribe an oracle to a coin pair. Delegates to the Oracle Manager smart contract.

totalMoc().notice: Get the value of the token, withdraw and deposit can be done only in multiples of the token value.

unsubscribeFromCoinPair(bytes32).notice: Unsubscribe an oracle from a coin pair. Delegates to the Oracle Manager smart contract.

withdraw(uint256).notice: Withdraw stake, send it to the delay machine.
